//
//   C — Averaged quad channel + scalar digest
//       Token: [mean_b0, mean_b1, D*] per 3-char triplet
//       mean_b0/mean_b1: quad transition codes (xu=00, xv=01,
//         xy=10, xz=11) averaged over 24 bit-positions per triplet
//       D*: fixed-point attractor digest, injected at word boundaries
//         only (zero elsewhere)
//       This is a LOSSY compression of the WOW signal — the per-bit
//       ternary is averaged away, the digest is sparse. The iterator
//       still provides structural signal but at lower resolution.
//
//   A — Raw triplet tokens, learned D=3 embedding
//       Standard baseline: 3-char windows, embedding table trained
//       end-to-end. No iterator involvement.
//
